name: KURT COBAIN
description:
Kurt Donald Cobain was an American musician. He was the frontman of the rock band Nirvana, serving as the band's guitarist, lead vocalist, and primary songwriter. Through his angst-fueled songwriting and anti-establishment persona, Cobain's compositions widened the thematic conventions of mainstream rock music. 
Born: February 20, 1967, Aberdeen, Washington, United States
Died: April 5, 1994, Seattle, Washington, United States
